import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='x', y='y', hue='name', palette='tab10', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Name', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lumosity', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['lumosity'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of lumosity?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=color_counts.index, y=color_counts.values, palette=color_counts.index)
    plt.xlabel('Color')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of color?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.countplot(x='key', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of key?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Key')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Key', loc='upper right', labels=data['key'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
